# Script conventions

## Overview

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `deploy-fast.sh` | Full image build + container recreate (frontend + backend) |
| `sync-backend.sh` | Hot-copy Python source into a running container (backend only) |
| `smoke-test.sh` | Container health check, optional HTTP probe |
| `recreate_container.py` | Inspect running container, recreate with new image preserving runtime config |

## Environment variables

| Variable | Default | Used by |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `IMAGE_TAG` | `baserow-custom:2.1.6-color-field` | `deploy-fast.sh` |
| `CONTAINER_NAME` | `baserow` | all scripts |
| `BASEROW_VERSION` | `2.1.6` | `deploy-fast.sh` (Docker build-arg) |
| `BASE_URL` | *(empty)* | `smoke-test.sh` (optional HTTP check) |

## Key constraints

- **`recreate_container.py`** introspects the existing container's binds, ports, env, restart policy, network, entrypoint, and command, then recreates with the same config on the new image. Do not simplify this to a bare `docker run` — it would lose the user's runtime configuration.
- **`sync-backend.sh`** copies source to **two** container paths (plugin dir + site-packages). Both must be updated together; removing one breaks either the plugin loader or Python imports.
- **`smoke-test.sh`** must stay idempotent with no side-effects. It only reads container state and optionally probes HTTP.
- All scripts use `set -euo pipefail`. Preserve this; do not add `|| true` to mask failures unless there is an explicit reason.
